    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Patients were either admitted directly, if belonging to the Rabat-Sal\u00e9 region (direct admission), or referred from regional hospitals (indirect admission). Prior to admission, patients undergo medical history checking and fever testing.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Admission Profiles and Measures ::: ORGANIZATION",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Admitted patients belonged to 2 groups: those requiring immediate surgical procedure (group A) and those requiring urgent but still scheduled surgery (group B).",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Emergency Case Definition and Stratification ::: ORGANIZATION",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Admission was limited to a maximum of 2 patients per room.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Circuit for Patient Management ::: ORGANIZATION",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Group A patients were operated in the emergency operating room (OR) and group B patients were operated in the mean operating theatre, directly connected to the intensive care unit (ICU).",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Circuit for Patient Management ::: ORGANIZATION",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Discharge was made early, and patients followed up over regular phone calls. The patient's bed and room were then thoroughly sterilized and kept free of patients for at least 24 h.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Circuit for Patient Management ::: ORGANIZATION",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "During hospitalization, only 1 visitor per day/patient was allowed. All wore protective masks.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Circuit for Patient Management ::: ORGANIZATION",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "African health systems needed to take proactive measures to lower the impact of such a disease.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "DISCUSSION",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "However, many of the recommendations published by other neurosurgical centers could not be achieved given the local limitations and resources.1-4",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 142,
                    "end": 145,
                    "mention": "1-4",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF0"
                }
            ],
            "section": "DISCUSSION",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "We believe that systematic pulmonary computed tomography (CT) scan helped initially in assessing a patient's COVID-19 status.1,5 COVID-19 testing further reinforced the algorithms set up by the local committee and accelerated the diagnosis of suspected cases.",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 125,
